When we study literature through text mining, our conclusions are not based on an examination of \'93literature\'94 itself, but on the corpus which is a sample or model of the imagined whole of \'93literature.\'94 Despite the importance of corpus-building to the interpretation of text mining research, it is often extremely difficult to know what is in a corpus. Even large institutional resources used by many scholars provide little context for their choices of what to include or exclude. These hidden choices are particularly problematic when historical selection factors might have led to the creation of corpora which re-create social inequalities.\cf3 \
